race.comment: OCEAN BEAR (2) made it two wins in succession last start when he scored by 1.75 lengths over 1308m at Santa Anita (Dirt). Winning rider Umberto Rispoli retains the mount. Going up a level this time but he can win again. THIRSTY REBEL (9) is a talented colt who tackled tougher grade last time, finishing 6 lengths behind Later Than Planned over 1006m in Listed grade at Santa Anita (Turf). Winning rider Abel Lezcano sticks. Bold showing expected. SAMMY DAVIS (6) finished 2 lengths away in fifth last time out over 1106m at this track after being in contention on the bend eight weeks ago as $2.4 favourite. Steps up in distance today. Hector Isaac Berrios who has two wins when partnering stays on. One of the contenders. FIONELLO (3) was below his best last time, finishing sixth and beaten 8 lengths over 1308m at Santa Anita (Dirt). Best figures measure up nicely. Solid top-three prospects.
